Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.18,0:00:06.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Star" is a fascinating word.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.83,0:00:08.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can refer to both culprits and actors!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.54,0:00:10.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Through reasoning, we finally\Nmake it to the Two Kings' treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.31,0:00:11.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But who will get it? Will it be Kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.44,0:00:12.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or will it be the Detective Boys?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.99,0:00:14.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing through to the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.48,0:00:16.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I look like a child, but have the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.20,0:00:18.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.21,0:00:23.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we felt the same light the moment we met.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.10,0:00:29.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, lots and lots of the same emotions filled our eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.85,0:00:35.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although the signals you sent destroyed my theory...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.75,0:00:41.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These feelings were always beyond your reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.74,0:00:47.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, let's fight, go against our morals...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.78,0:00:52.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And aim for a wider world!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.30,0:00:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, glimmering star, shine over us forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.15,0:01:05.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, we won't lose the dreams we had when we were young...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.13,0:01:11.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't care if this town changes someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.10,0:01:17.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only thing I don't want to change is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.20,0:01:23.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, glimmering star, shine over us forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.90,0:01:29.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, we won't lose the dreams we had when we were young...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.00,0:01:39.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,1350)}The only thing I don't want to change is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.51,0:01:46.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We went to camp with Professor Agasa.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.10,0:01:49.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nearby, at an odd mansion, Genta\Nand the others found a strange stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.11,0:01:54.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inside, we found a coded\Nmessage leading to the "Big Jewel"...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.48,0:01:59.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And right next to it, we found the body of a\Nman who had been mysteriously murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.24,0:02:03.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, we decided to go in the\Nodd mansion and began to explore it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.41,0:02:08.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There, we met two treasure\Nhunters and a strange old woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.17,0:02:14.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, we really do have to find one\Nmore of the Regalia to solve this mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.88,0:02:16.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"One more...?"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.51,0:02:18.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The third of the Three Imperial Regalia.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.63,0:02:22.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We already found the mirror\Nand the comma-shaped magatama...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.14,0:02:24.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So there has to be one more somewhere around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.22,0:02:25.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Three Imperial Regalia?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.43,0:02:27.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.31,0:02:29.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hEight Hand Mirror\NThe mirror is known as the "Yata no Kagami"...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.19,0:02:31.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hTear of Benevolence\NThe magatama is known as the "Yasakani no Magatama"...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.73,0:02:33.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the last one remaining...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.90,0:02:37.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Long ago, when a treacherous\Nwarlord set a grassy plain on fire...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.19,0:02:40.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to send Yamato-dake Mikoto to his\Ndemise by trapping him in the ensuing blaze...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.45,0:02:42.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He used a sword to mow the grass...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.16,0:02:43.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ultimately saving himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.53,0:02:45.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the divine sword:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.74,0:02:47.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,\h\h\hGrass-Mowing Sword\NThe "Kusanagi no Tsurugi".
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.96,0:02:51.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Big Adventure at the Unconventional Mansion:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.17,0:02:52.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Solution Part!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.29,0:02:55.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.50,0:02:57.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know about the Kusanagi no Tsurugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.76,0:03:00.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the really powerful sword\Nthat's in video games a lot, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.63,0:03:03.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Kusanagi no Tsurugi?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.96,0:03:07.94,CharCards01 shadow,,0,0,0,,Akutsu Sarina (29)\N{\fs16}\h\h\h\hTreasure Hunter\h\h\h\h
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.42,0:03:08.18,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,We may figure something out if we find that sword and see which character is engraved on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.18,0:03:11.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before hunting for the treasure...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.19,0:03:16.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be better if we combined our\Npower and found a way out of this dungeon?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.32,0:03:19.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, if it's about getting out of this place...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.44,0:03:21.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy should know a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.15,0:03:22.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.41,0:03:28.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this was actually your first time coming here,\Nand didn't know you needed to find one more character...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.24,0:03:31.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't have had any reason to hide\Nthat stone mirror so preciously, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.52,0:03:35.01,CharCards02 shadow,,0,0,0,,Sutou Unzou (40)\N{\fs17}\h\h\hTreasure Hunter\h\h\h
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.21,0:03:33.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.75,0:03:35.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.59,0:03:40.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this sure is a huge mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.59,0:03:43.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The basement is unexpectedly large.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.76,0:03:47.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? The floor is wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.31,0:03:48.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.01,0:03:50.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where is that water coming from?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.14,0:03:51.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There, it's from over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.77,0:03:56.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this? It looks like it cracked...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.15,0:04:01.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, now that you mention it...\NThere was an earthquake a few days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.74,0:04:05.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It caused the mansion to shift a bit, and\Nmade some water start flooding the basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.27,0:04:11.40,CharCards03 shadow,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,350)}\h\h\hSenju Eri(72)\h\h\h\N{\fs17}\h\h\hTreasure Hunter\h\h\h
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.18,0:04:09.37,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That exactly what Kichiemon{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.50,0:04:12.50,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Don't you think that was caused\Nby "the wrath of the Two Kings"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.60,0:04:16.20,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's why you should stop looking for\Nthe treasure and quickly get back home!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.88,0:04:25.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, the notebook that the guy who\Ndrowned in the sunk in the lake was carrying...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.09,0:04:26.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It dried off, so I was able to read what he wrote in it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.14,0:04:31.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it seems like that guy really was killed by his partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.68,0:04:36.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Regretfully, I teamed up with someone awful.\NIf I don't hide this stone I found, I know they'll kill me."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.90,0:04:42.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"This little rat said they want to kill me so he\Ncan find the treasure and keep it all for their self..."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.40,0:04:46.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like there was more after that,\Nbut the page got torn, so I can't read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.28,0:04:49.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Woah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.04,0:04:52.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.75,0:04:54.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Way awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.34,0:05:02.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hot water... Is this a hot spring?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.01,0:05:02.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.71,0:05:05.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kichiemon probably dug it himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.93,0:05:10.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to hide the exit with this hot water.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.72,0:05:11.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.60,0:05:12.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure is amazing, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.47,0:05:15.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides that, the hot spring water is red, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.44,0:05:17.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if it has a high iron content...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.86,0:05:19.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.81,0:05:21.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not the way to the exit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.19,0:05:22.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.40,0:05:28.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.91,0:05:31.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.91,0:05:33.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.83,0:05:36.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know where the Kusanagi no Tsurugi came from?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.50,0:05:37.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.83,0:05:40.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You guys had to have heard the story before...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.29,0:05:42.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to save Princess Kushinada...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.84,0:05:46.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amaterasu Oomikami's\Nyounger brother, Susanoo Nomikoto...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.17,0:05:49.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forced the serpent that was holding her\Ncaptive to drink alcohol, then exterminated it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.84,0:05:55.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "Kusanagi no Tsurugi" was\Nthen found inside that serpent's tail...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.73,0:05:57.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hSword of the Gathering Clouds Of Heaven\NBut was originally called the "Ama no Murakomo no Tsurugi".
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.81,0:06:01.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could that serpent be the same\None that's in many of the old legends?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.48,0:06:02.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.32,0:06:05.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one with eyes as red as rubies...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.19,0:06:06.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With a stomach that longs for blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.82,0:06:11.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The legendary serpent that has one\Nbody with eight heads and eight tails.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.20,0:06:13.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at this waterfall...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.83,0:06:15.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't it look remarkably similar?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.12,0:06:19.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To the Eight-Headed Serpent, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.75,0:06:25.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.42,0:06:29.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if the waterfalls are the snake's necks,\Nthese tributaries are its tails, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.93,0:06:32.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the sword is in one of these tributaries?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.85,0:06:37.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. And according to the legend,\Nthe sword was found in the center tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.35,0:06:41.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the Kusanagi no Tsurugi must be in this tributary.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.60,0:06:44.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you intend to dive into the hot water?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.32,0:06:45.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop, stop...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.78,0:06:47.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.40,0:06:50.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What will you do if it leads to the bottom of the valley?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.41,0:06:54.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But since we've come this far,\Nwe wanna see what's over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.00,0:07:08.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something is rising.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.01,0:07:10.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the water level is decreasing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.72,0:07:16.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can walk through the tunnel, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.64,0:07:17.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.06,0:07:19.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, I'll go first!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.73,0:07:21.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, Genta!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.19,0:07:23.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Move it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.94,0:07:26.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Granny!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.19,0:07:27.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.86,0:07:44.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that has to be... {\t(1500,1501,}the Kusanagi no Tsurugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.05,0:07:59.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought, the old woman is aiming for the treasure too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.06,0:08:03.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's a really troublesome trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.06,0:08:07.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we get closer to the sword,\Nwe'll be putting weight on the floor around it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.02,0:08:09.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Causing us to get attacked by\Nblades coming from all four directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.53,0:08:11.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like we can't pass, can we?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.82,0:08:13.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.24,0:08:16.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The trap isn't there just to get us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.08,0:08:19.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The blades may come from all four directions...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.62,0:08:21.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.37,0:08:23.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And seemingly cover every part of the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.46,0:08:28.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if you find the absolute\Nperfect timing, you won't get hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.88,0:08:31.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.38,0:08:35.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since there's such a conveniently-placed handle here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.76,0:08:40.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can simply utilize the blade and\Nactually have it take you right to the sword!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.44,0:08:48.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.44,0:08:49.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He made it to the other side!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.98,0:08:52.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you're amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.78,0:08:55.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What character is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.16,0:08:56.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's written on the sword?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.25,0:09:04.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ryuu\NDragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.34,0:09:05.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Ryuu...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.26,0:09:07.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ryuu.?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.25,0:09:10.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eternity \hFlame\h \h\h\hDragon\h\h\N"Ei", "honoo", and "ryuu"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.67,0:09:15.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As expected from Kichiemon{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.47,0:09:20.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd be in pain for all eternity if you were\Nburnt by the dragon's flames, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.47,0:09:25.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? Let's stop looking for the treasure and go back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.31,0:09:28.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There probably wasn't even a\Ntreasure there in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.94,0:09:30.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.40,0:09:33.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her eyes were gleaming over\Nthe treasure a few minutes ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.53,0:09:38.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Wandering person, offer me the Three Imperial Regalia."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.58,0:09:43.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ei... {\t(1200,1201,}Honoo.. {\t(2500,2501,}Ryuu.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.92,0:09:43.88,Ei,,0,0,0,,{\fade(480,0)}Ei
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.92,0:09:43.88,Eternity,,0,0,0,,{\fade(480,0)}Eternity
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.20,0:09:43.88,Honoo,,0,0,0,,{\fade(480,0)}Honoo
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.20,0:09:43.88,Flame,,0,0,0,,{\fade(480,0)}Flame
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.44,0:09:43.88,Ryuu,,0,0,0,,{\fade(480,0)}Ryuu
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.44,0:09:43.88,Dragon,,0,0,0,,{\fade(480,0)}Dragon
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.37,0:09:46.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Offer me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.12,0:09:48.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Me!"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.46,0:09:51.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.67,0:09:52.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.97,0:09:58.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you get back over here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.45,0:10:19.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's that proud, smug-looking face...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.41,0:10:20.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You figured something out, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.95,0:10:22.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.78,0:10:23.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.74,0:10:27.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the face of someone who was defeated\Nand has to go home with their tail between their legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.00,0:10:31.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.21,0:10:33.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.92,0:10:36.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are we really heading back?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.09,0:10:40.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right when we finally found\Nthe Three Imperial Regalia, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.39,0:10:42.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are we giving up on finding the diamond?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.14,0:10:48.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, the meaning of the characters\Nengraved on the Regalia: "honoo", "ei", and "ryuu"...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.06,0:10:51.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As well as what was written\Ninside the Japanese stone lantern...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.40,0:10:55.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't understand a single word of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.36,0:10:57.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, I'll take my leave here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.53,0:11:03.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess I'll check out this mansion a little more.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.08,0:11:08.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're finally out of there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.04,0:11:11.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like the Professor hasn't come back yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.71,0:11:12.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Professor?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.38,0:11:17.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, the Professor was supposed\Nto have brought policemen here, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.09,0:11:22.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? Then, you won't need an old\Nwoman like me to escort you off this mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.30,0:11:28.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you haven't already been cursed by the Two Kings,\Nyou'd better not loiter around and hurry back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.35,0:11:34.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, now that all those\Npeople aren't here to get in our way...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.06,0:11:35.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it about time you guided us there?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.94,0:11:39.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To the treasure, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.69,0:11:41.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.70,0:11:44.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Edogawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.45,0:11:51.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you really...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.16,0:11:53.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Solved it, didn't you? That coded message!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.33,0:11:56.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was from what was written on\Nthe gravestone in the basement:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.92,0:11:59.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Wandering person, offer me the Three Imperial Regalia."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.70,0:12:07.73,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFFFF&\3c&HC82E24&\fade(300,300)}Note: In kanji "Samizu" can also be read as "Sanzui" becomes a radical for water\Nwhich, when attached to another kanji, changes its reading and meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.55,0:12:04.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This "me" refers to "Samizu" from Samizu Kichiemon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.14,0:12:07.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It basically means to "attach the sanzui\Nradical to the kanji of the Three Imperial Regalia".
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.14,0:12:11.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The three characters we found on the\NThree Imperial Regalia were "honoo" and what else?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.27,0:12:12.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,\h\h\h\h\h\h\hEternity\N"Ei" from "eien"!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.82,0:12:14.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dragon\h\h\NAnd "ryuu", right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.90,0:12:17.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if you attach the sanzui, or water radical...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.48,0:12:22.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Honoo" becomes the "awa" from Awajishima Island!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.90,0:12:21.60,Flame 2,,0,0,0,,{\fade(170,150)}Flame
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.60,0:12:22.46,Awa,,0,0,0,,{\fade(170,0)}Awa
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.73,0:12:23.21,Awa,,0,0,0,,Awa
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.48,0:12:23.96,Awa,,0,0,0,,Awa
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.23,0:12:24.42,Awa,,0,0,0,,Awa
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.43,0:12:25.78,Eternity 2,,0,0,0,,{\fade(180,150)}Eternity
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.79,0:12:26.63,Swimming,,0,0,0,,{\fade(150,0)}Swimming
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.90,0:12:27.38,Swimming,,0,0,0,,Swimming
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.63,0:12:28.13,Swimming,,0,0,0,,Swimming
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.40,0:12:28.63,Swimming,,0,0,0,,Swimming
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.49,0:12:26.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hSwimming\N"Ei" is the "ei" in "suiei"!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.29,0:12:31.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Waterfall\N"Ryuu" is "taki", isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.40,0:12:31.05,Dragon 2,,0,0,0,,{\fade(180,100)}Dragon
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.06,0:12:31.88,Dragon 2,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,0)}Waterfall
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.15,0:12:32.63,Dragon 2,,0,0,0,,Waterfall
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.90,0:12:33.38,Dragon 2,,0,0,0,,Waterfall
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.87,0:12:33.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.42,0:12:36.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does that mean we can swim\Nat Aojishima Island's waterfall?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.66,0:12:34.59,Dragon 2,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,350)}Waterfall
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.21,0:12:39.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The gravestone had "Wandering person" on it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.96,0:12:43.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was a hint to help those who couldn't\Nfigure out the code on the Japanese stone lantern.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.38,0:12:49.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Japanese stone lantern basically said it's at "the place\Nclosest to the sun, a bustling place where elders gather."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.35,0:12:53.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we take that into account with the three\Ncharacters we just found and think about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.70,0:12:58.35,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFFFF&\3c&HC82E24&\fade(300,300)}Note: The Japanese word for Mercury is "Suisei".\N"Sui" means fresh water, while "sei" means planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.94,0:12:57.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The closest place to the sun is the\Nfirst planet in the solar system, Mercury...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.90,0:13:01.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Elders" means something that has a\Nbeard, which is referring to a "carp".
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.36,0:13:04.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bustling place means a place\Nwhere the fresh water makes a lot of noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.86,0:13:10.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, close to a school of carp that are swimming\Naround the place where the waterfall is noisiest...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.33,0:13:14.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hides the Two Kings' stone, the diamond!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.37,0:13:15.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's amazing, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.79,0:13:17.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it's at the waterfall in the basement!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.17,0:13:19.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Eight-Headed Serpent place, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.29,0:13:22.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, that's a hot spring, not fresh water.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.01,0:13:26.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Couldn't it be in the river inside the house, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.80,0:13:29.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, a whole bunch of carp were swimming there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.85,0:13:32.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there wasn't a waterfall around there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.64,0:13:34.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.14,0:13:37.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen? Don't turn your ears away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.77,0:13:38.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can hear it, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.69,0:13:41.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thing that will lead us to the treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.65,0:13:43.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.15,0:13:46.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.32,0:13:48.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the lake we saw when we first came here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.74,0:13:49.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go and see!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.29,0:13:55.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.04,0:13:57.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That corpse disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.83,0:13:59.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.33,0:14:03.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit must have hid it after we went in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.25,0:14:04.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.76,0:14:07.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"A corpse"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.05,0:14:11.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you see something?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.71,0:14:12.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.97,0:14:16.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's very dark, so we can't see if we don't dive in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.18,0:14:17.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a shame...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.65,0:14:23.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it looks like someone got here before us, somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.36,0:14:24.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.57,0:14:26.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lady from earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.28,0:14:27.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When did you get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.11,0:14:30.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a look behind the waterfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.49,0:14:31.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Behind the waterfall?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.45,0:14:34.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's something that looks like a card there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.95,0:14:38.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I've taken the Two Kings' Stone."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.75,0:14:40.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kaitou Kid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.42,0:14:41.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.67,0:14:42.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.71,0:14:43.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.88,0:14:48.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As expected from the great thief from the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.84,0:14:52.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since this was taken by.\Nsomeone using the name of "Kaitou"...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.47,0:14:55.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This should satisfy Karakuri Kichiemon{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.22,0:14:59.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Granny hadn't gone back home yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.10,0:14:59.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.90,0:15:03.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.19,0:15:05.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.50,0:15:21.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.83,0:15:24.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.04,0:15:26.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like there's nothing else here for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.67,0:15:30.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.35,0:15:36.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was covered in mud...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.35,0:15:39.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there really was a\Nshiny-looking stone at the bottom of the lake!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.19,0:15:44.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.56,0:15:46.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't take it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.94,0:15:48.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.11,0:15:50.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The person who does not\Nfear the wrath of the Two Kings..."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.74,0:15:54.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"In order to take possession of the\Nstone that will fill one's hand to the fullest..."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.49,0:15:57.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"You must understand its origin, from long ago."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.12,0:15:59.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Its origin, from long ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.96,0:16:04.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop, don't move a muscle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.75,0:16:08.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who would have thought it was hidden\Nin the mud at the bottom of a waterfall?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.38,0:16:12.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a dangerous place, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.13,0:16:14.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I was tricked by that card, so I\Nguess I didn't search thoroughly enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.76,0:16:19.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So line up there!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.64,0:16:23.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As soon as that guy comes out with the jewel in his hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.90,0:16:26.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about I send you guys go down\Nthere with him, to swim with the fishes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.57,0:16:30.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you've finally made your appearance...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.03,0:16:30.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kaitou Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.57,0:16:33.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That lady is...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.70,0:16:36.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? I'm Kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.16,0:16:37.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You idiots, I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.41,0:16:42.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the "little rat" of a treasure hunter who killed\Ntheir partner, just to have the treasure all to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.62,0:16:43.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.54,0:16:47.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you the one who said it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.63,0:16:50.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When that guy first showed us the stone mirror...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.97,0:16:54.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the comma-shaped magatama you guys found...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.84,0:16:57.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was engraved with "honoo"\Nor something like that, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.55,0:16:58.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.06,0:17:04.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, I only said I found a\Nstone from the Three Imperial Regalia.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.44,0:17:06.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you know beforehand?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.23,0:17:08.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That it was the comma-shaped\Nmagatama, and not the sword?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.86,0:17:14.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew because you had torn a page out of the\Nnotebook of the man we found drowned in the lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.20,0:17:19.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The page where he drew a comma-shaped\Nmagatama with the "honoo" character inside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.45,0:17:23.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you know what he wrote in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.96,0:17:31.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was writing in the notebook with a pencil,\Nso faint marks would be imprinted on the opposite page.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.13,0:17:35.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're kind of smart...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.30,0:17:36.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you're really careless, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.97,0:17:39.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You keep getting ever closer to the muzzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.76,0:17:40.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.60,0:17:41.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if I didn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.69,0:17:55.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't have been able to aim my\Ntranquilizer watch straight at you, now would I?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.70,0:18:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that really surprised me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.95,0:18:04.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the lady being Kid and all...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.66,0:18:06.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, Kid is-
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.25,0:18:11.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got the Two Kings' Stone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.84,0:18:13.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This isn't good!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.57,0:18:37.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry, and put the diamond back where you found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.49,0:18:38.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.07,0:18:41.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise this water is going to sweep us away,\Nall the way down to the bottom of the valley!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.87,0:18:50.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! Here it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.00,0:18:52.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is this mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.44,0:19:15.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That diamond was the switch for that big flood gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.69,0:19:20.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, he didn't have any intention\Nof letting us take the diamond in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.57,0:19:26.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, diamonds are known for being harder\Nthan anything else, so they were called "adamasu"...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.75,0:19:29.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which basically meant that they\Nwere "something no one can conquer".
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.25,0:19:34.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So "understanding its origin" meant that\Nthere's absolutely no way we could take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.13,0:19:36.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, back in his day...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.71,0:19:39.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toba Kanizae{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} ordered the seizure of\Nthe Shogunate's assets after its collapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.67,0:19:43.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Being one of their financial supporters,\NKichiemon thought of this to protect his fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.76,0:19:47.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that why you stopped trying to get it, Granny?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.60,0:19:51.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the great thief of the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.16,0:20:04.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-He came!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.45,0:20:05.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kaitou Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.91,0:20:08.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Great logic, you were right on the mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.91,0:20:14.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fact that the mansion's walls were a little\Nhigher than the water leak in the basement path...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.17,0:20:17.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That fact that you left your signature card,\Neven though you didn't take the jewel...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.67,0:20:21.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that there was a person who kept\Ntelling us not to take it, all pointed to one thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.93,0:20:25.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Granny was really Kaitou Kid in disguise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.35,0:20:28.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Correct!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.39,0:20:32.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But part of the reason I didn't take\Nit is because I have no interest in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.94,0:20:37.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you said to stop looking for\Nthe treasure and head back home, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.65,0:20:41.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But didn't he push me out of the way\Nso he could hurry and get the sword?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.15,0:20:44.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was to save you, Genta.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.61,0:20:45.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.53,0:20:48.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you had rushed in and stepped\Non the trigger without noticing...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.12,0:20:50.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't you have been cut into\Neight pieces and sent to the other world?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.79,0:20:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he was waiting for us in the basement so we\Nwouldn't do anything that'd get us caught in the traps!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.73,0:20:58.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, my...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.88,0:21:01.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a very heart-warming thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.59,0:21:04.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm very flattered by your compliment, little lady...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.72,0:21:09.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, you saved my friends, so I'll give\Nyou my thanks and let you go this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.31,0:21:15.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But one day, I'll definitely catch\Nyou and investigate your true identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.90,0:21:23.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right before I rip off that arrogant monocle\Nof yours and look at your true face, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.03,0:21:25.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd better not.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.41,0:21:30.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like Pandora's Box, you want to open\Nit because you don't know what's inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.58,0:21:33.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if you know what's inside before you open it...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.59,0:21:41.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's boring, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.68,0:21:49.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot, knowing the facts before exposing someone...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.55,0:21:52.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,ls the job of a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.39,0:22:03.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before I knew it, I had come to the riverside of memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.90,0:22:12.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Imagining a continuation of yesterday's dream...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.12,0:22:19.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You seemed so grown-up when you were a boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.75,0:22:25.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't say goodbye, so I hid under my umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.97,0:22:31.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we ever meet again, just please remember
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.64,0:22:34.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,all those times, and don't forget me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.14,0:22:44.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My love and affection are things that will never change.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.40,0:22:55.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You are my one and only love, and that's how it will always be.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.25,0:23:05.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like many people, I reminisce while holding on to my feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.01,0:23:18.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So l can keep the memory of us meeting from fading away.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.35,0:23:21.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, what do we do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.81,0:23:22.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.98,0:23:26.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I put the jewel back where I found it,\Nso it seems the water level is decreasing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.69,0:23:29.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like we have no other choice\Nbut to wait for someone to find us.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.07,0:23:32.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right! What about the Professor?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.46,0:23:44.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on to the tree as tight as you can!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.55,0:23:49.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was the owner of this room,\NOzawa Fumie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, 24 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.92,0:23:51.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was a secretary who worked for a trading company.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.35,0:24:00.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She put it on vibrate? Even when she's in her house?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.90,0:24:06.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's either Madam or Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, but which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.61,0:24:07.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah-le-le?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.73,0:24:10.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle, whatever could this be?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.07,0:24:16.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan: Spicy, Bitter & Sweet Soup.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.95,0:24:19.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.45,0:24:21.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Powder.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.08,0:24:26.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please look forward to the next episode!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.12,0:24:22.19,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Guys, what are you doing for Golden Week?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.19,0:24:22.71,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.74,0:24:23.13,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,We're going...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.16,0:24:23.58,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,To the movies!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.61,0:24:25.71,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Strategy Above The Depths!
